de.saxsys.mvvmfx.utils.commands

Class CompositeCommand

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.saxsys.mvvmfx.utils.commands.CommandBase
      • de.saxsys.mvvmfx.utils.commands.CompositeCommand
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Command

    @Beta
public class CompositeCommand
extends CommandBase
    CompositeCommand is an aggregation of other commands - a list of Command references internally.

    It allows you to hook up multiple command targets to a single root command that itself can be hooked up to a command source such as a button or menu item.

    The CompositeCommand can hold references to any object but typically you will use it in conjunction with DelegateCommands.

    When the execute() method is invoked it will invoke the Command.execute() method on each of the child commands.

    When CommandBase.isExecutable() is called to determine whether the command is enabled, it polls its child commands for their result from CommandBase.isExecutable().

    Author:
    alexander.casall
